  "text": "An important morphological feature of the ON and OFF retinal systems starts within the inner plexiform layer (IPL). Two segregated layers receive the cone inputs in which the ON and OFF cone-bipolar cells make their synaptic contacts with the ON and OFF ganglion cells (Figure 1) . The OFF cone-bipolar cells synapse with the OFF ganglion cells at the more proximal sublayer (region called sublamina a) while the cone-bipolar ON cells synapse with the ON ganglion cells at the more distal sublayer (sublamina b) [2] [CITATION_1] [4] .",
